1
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:29,550
<i>Like all things on this hurtling sphere...</i>

2
00:00:29,720 --> 00:00:33,380
<i>...I emerged from the molten center
of creation.</i>

3
00:00:34,670 --> 00:00:37,420
<i>But mine has been a unique path.</i>

4
00:00:37,590 --> 00:00:42,930
<i>Isolated, I developed attributes
beyond those of lesser beings.</i>

5
00:00:46,590 --> 00:00:50,630
<i>Then the sphere was struck
by a vast celestial stone.</i>

6
00:00:53,340 --> 00:00:57,050
<i>Black chunks of death filled the skies...</i>

7
00:00:57,220 --> 00:01:00,930
<i>...and the world
became a chaotic garden of doom.</i>

8
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:06,260
<i>Soon the sphere began
to nurture new kinds of life.</i>

9
00:01:06,420 --> 00:01:09,140
<i>And there was one
that stood above all the rest.</i>

10
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:12,420
<i>Its fragile shell belied its vicious nature.</i>

11
00:01:12,590 --> 00:01:14,510
<i>And in what seemed like a heartbeat...</i>

12
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:20,010
<i>...these things proliferated in both number
and destructive means.</i>

13
00:01:22,590 --> 00:01:26,420
<i>Now they have harnessed
the most destructive force.</i>

14
00:01:27,930 --> 00:01:31,930
<i>And I, The Centre, have concluded...</i>

15
00:01:32,090 --> 00:01:35,720
<i>...that the sphere
must be cleansed of them.</i>

16
00:04:02,220 --> 00:04:04,970
<i>This is Lois Lane on Armed Forces Radio.</i>

17
00:04:05,140 --> 00:04:08,970
<i>Well, boys, it looks like the party's over.
They signed the ceasefire.</i>

18
00:04:09,140 --> 00:04:11,590
<i>So have a drink and smoke them
if you got them.</i>

19
00:04:11,930 --> 00:04:14,140
<i>We're going home.</i>

20
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:24,140
Some way to end a war, huh, kid?
Nobody wins, nobody loses.

21
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:26,800
Long as it's over, Ace. I got plans.

22
00:04:26,970 --> 00:04:29,460
Right, I forgot.
You're gonna be a space ranger.

23
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:33,220
The proper term is "test pilot,"
funny man.

24
00:04:33,590 --> 00:04:36,970
I'm gonna see the stars, close up.

25
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:39,880
Hey.

26
00:04:43,380 --> 00:04:45,970
Sons of bitches must not have heard
about the ceasefire.

27
00:04:49,590 --> 00:04:53,340
<i>I'm coming back for you.
Try using your guns for a change.</i>

28
00:05:06,460 --> 00:05:07,970
<i>Can you make it back now, Ace?</i>

29
00:05:08,180 --> 00:05:10,760
Roger that.
Gotta get me a new pair of skivvies.

30
00:05:12,420 --> 00:05:14,260
Got another bogey.

31
00:05:19,550 --> 00:05:21,670
<i>Hal, your engine.</i>

32
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:23,180
<i>Punch out. Punch out!</i>

33
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:11,300
Listen to me. War over.

34
00:06:12,630 --> 00:06:14,050
Finished.

35
00:06:33,140 --> 00:06:34,760
It's over.

36
00:06:35,340 --> 00:06:38,010
War over.

37
00:07:01,670 --> 00:07:03,930
I'm so sorry.

38
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:09,090
All I wanted was to send a signal
to Mars.

39
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:13,970
How could I have known
it would teleport you here?

40
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:20,970
I suppose we both got the shock
of our lives.

41
00:07:22,140 --> 00:07:26,930
But your heart must be stronger
than mine.

42
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:29,880
Whoever you are...

43
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:33,970
...forgive me.

44
00:08:29,510 --> 00:08:30,670
Come on in, Kal.

45
00:08:31,380 --> 00:08:33,180
Join the celebration.

46
00:08:33,630 --> 00:08:35,880
Diana, what's going on here?

47
00:08:36,460 --> 00:08:38,460
Tell them they'd be wasting their bullets.

48
00:08:40,260 --> 00:08:43,800
Don't judge them, KaI.
They get a little nervous around men now.

49
00:08:44,050 --> 00:08:46,550
What are you talking about?
-I was heading upriver...

50
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:49,050
...when I passed this village
about four days ago.

51
00:08:49,220 --> 00:08:52,050
The people here helped the French.
The rebels didn't like that.

52
00:08:52,220 --> 00:08:55,380
They murdered the men and children
and they threw them in the river.

53
00:08:55,550 --> 00:09:01,010
<i>These women were beaten and penned
in tiger cages for the rebels to use.</i>

54
00:09:02,050 --> 00:09:04,300
<i>The rebels, how did they die?</i>

55
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:05,970
<i>I only disarmed them.</i>

56
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:11,880
<i>I left their guns in a clearing and
then I let the women out of their cages.</i>

57
00:09:17,460 --> 00:09:19,140
They did this?

58
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:21,340
And you just stood by and watched?

59
00:09:21,510 --> 00:09:23,760
I gave them freedom
and a chance for justice.

60
00:09:23,930 --> 00:09:27,140
You know, the American way.

61
00:09:27,510 --> 00:09:30,140
This is what the government's afraid of,
Diana.

62
00:09:30,300 --> 00:09:32,380
Us acting like vigilantes.

63
00:09:32,550 --> 00:09:34,550
I have to do what I think is right.

64
00:09:34,970 --> 00:09:37,220
That's what the others said at first,
remember?

65
00:09:37,510 --> 00:09:40,760
And now Batman's a fugitive,
the whole Justice Society's retired...

66
00:09:40,930 --> 00:09:42,880
...and Hourman's dead.

67
00:09:43,380 --> 00:09:44,840
No matter how much good we do...

68
00:09:45,010 --> 00:09:48,050
...deep down, people are always
going to be scared of us.

69
00:09:48,380 --> 00:09:51,220
Isn't that why you and I
signed those loyalty oaths?

70
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:52,720
Take a look around, Kal.

71
00:09:53,340 --> 00:09:55,340
Oaths don't mean much here.

72
00:09:55,510 --> 00:09:57,760
All I see is suffering and madness.

73
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:01,460
But...
-There's the door, spaceman.

74
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:04,760
Yeah.

75
00:10:04,930 --> 00:10:06,800
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

76
00:10:06,970 --> 00:10:08,510
Yeah.

77
00:10:51,140 --> 00:10:55,630
<i>The downed pilot insisted
the island was teeming with dinosaurs...</i>

78
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:58,180
<i>...but Navy sources claim
a search revealed...</i>

79
00:10:58,340 --> 00:11:03,090
<i>...that not only were there no dinosaurs,
there wasn't even an island.</i>

80
00:11:03,260 --> 00:11:04,630
<i>In other news-</i>

81
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:08,010
<i>Well, I don't know, Groucho,
that's not really what I meant.</i>

82
00:11:08,180 --> 00:11:11,510
<i>We keep our farm animals in the farm,
not in the house.</i>

83
00:11:11,670 --> 00:11:13,970
<i>Not in the bedroom, certainly.</i>

84
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:18,800
<i>Eh, what's up, doc?</i>

85
00:11:22,090 --> 00:11:25,180
<i>This now concludes our broadcasting day.</i>

86
00:11:32,930 --> 00:11:35,550
The last I heard,
she went back to Paradise Island.

87
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:37,590
It sounds like she's lost her mind.

88
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:40,550
I don't think it's that simple.

89
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:43,050
Diana's an Amazon
who's become an American.

90
00:11:43,220 --> 00:11:45,550
She's trying to make sense
of her convictions.

91
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:48,670
Between her and that Batman character...

92
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:51,720
I thought these people were your friends.
-They are.

93
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:54,970
But neither of them would sacrifice
their principles for a friend.

94
00:11:55,140 --> 00:11:58,380
Ever since McCarthy came to-
-McCarthy. He's no excuse.

95
00:11:58,550 --> 00:12:02,880
Whatever party, whatever administration,
there'll always be boogeymen like him.

96
00:12:03,050 --> 00:12:04,840
We need our heroes to stand up...

97
00:12:04,970 --> 00:12:08,340
...and show us what this country
is supposed to mean.

98
00:12:11,420 --> 00:12:14,050
We need a leader.

99
00:12:31,930 --> 00:12:34,220
Come on, rolI it.
Come on, eight. Come on, eight.

100
00:12:34,380 --> 00:12:35,880
Yes.

101
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,670
Ten's the number to win.

102
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:42,340
Now why don't you tell me
what we're doing here, Ace?

103
00:12:42,510 --> 00:12:45,090
Told you, HaI, it's a surprise.

104
00:12:45,510 --> 00:12:46,800
You'll find out tomorrow.

105
00:12:47,260 --> 00:12:50,380
Now, roll those dice before they cool off.

106
00:12:54,340 --> 00:12:55,720
Come on, 10.

107
00:12:56,180 --> 00:12:58,180
Ten. It's a winner.

108
00:13:00,420 --> 00:13:02,880
And you have the loveliest light
in your eyes, dig?

109
00:13:03,050 --> 00:13:07,630
Can we get back to the interview, please?
-Oh, yeah. My philosophy of life.

110
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:11,050
Tell your readers they gotta do what I do,
live for the moment...

111
00:13:11,220 --> 00:13:14,220
...because it might be our last,
you dig, Miss West?

112
00:13:14,380 --> 00:13:16,550
Very profound.
-That's me.

113
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:20,970
I've always been, you know,
deep like that.

114
00:13:22,090 --> 00:13:23,550
Time for the sound check, boss.

115
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:29,930
Back in a moment.

116
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:32,460
I'll try to live for it.

117
00:13:34,010 --> 00:13:37,840
<i>I tell you, these two heavyweights
are giving us quite a show tonight.</i>

118
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:41,380
<i>Oh, it looks like it'Il have to wait
for the next round, folks.</i>

119
00:13:41,550 --> 00:13:43,090
<i>Meantime, we've got the champ...</i>

120
00:13:44,420 --> 00:13:46,550
<i>...Ted "Wildcat" Grant,
solidly ahead on points.</i>

121
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:48,180
<i>Uh, hello.
-Hello, Barry?</i>

122
00:13:48,340 --> 00:13:50,590
Iris. I thought you had to work tonight.

123
00:13:50,970 --> 00:13:52,010
I do.

124
00:13:52,180 --> 00:13:54,630
But I wanted to tell you
how much I miss you.

125
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:57,460
You have no idea.
-Come on, how could you miss me?

126
00:13:57,630 --> 00:14:00,760
You're in Las Vegas interviewing
all those singers and movie stars.

127
00:14:00,930 --> 00:14:01,970
<i>It's the fast lane.</i>

128
00:14:02,140 --> 00:14:05,590
There are lots of potholes
in that lane, let me tell you.

129
00:14:07,670 --> 00:14:09,180
Iris? Iris.

130
00:14:15,550 --> 00:14:19,720
Sorry to interrupt your festivities,
but if you all stay calm...

131
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:25,010
...we'll be gone as soon as my friends here
come back from the cashiers' booths.

132
00:14:29,340 --> 00:14:33,380
The key phrase was "stay calm. "

133
00:14:36,670 --> 00:14:37,970
<i>Iris, what's happening?</i>

134
00:14:38,300 --> 00:14:39,670
You there.

135
00:14:40,050 --> 00:14:42,720
The naughty girl on the phone.

136
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:46,140
Iris!

137
00:15:04,630 --> 00:15:06,760
Just a few more seconds, everyone.

138
00:15:08,380 --> 00:15:10,090
Ah, my ride is here.

139
00:15:25,260 --> 00:15:27,260
Wait.

140
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:29,340
Make it quick.

141
00:15:30,380 --> 00:15:33,340
Hot damn, Ace.
It's that super-fast guy from CentraI City.

142
00:15:33,550 --> 00:15:35,590
The Flash. He'll take care of this clown.

143
00:15:35,970 --> 00:15:38,140
I took precautions
in case you dropped by.

144
00:15:38,510 --> 00:15:39,930
If you so much as touch me...

145
00:15:40,090 --> 00:15:43,420
...you'Il trigger six cryogenic bombs
I've hidden around the city.

146
00:15:43,590 --> 00:15:47,140
And they'll go off in 90 seconds anyway,
unless you find them.

147
00:15:47,510 --> 00:15:53,460
So it's your choice now.
Me, or the city and everyone in it.

148
00:15:53,630 --> 00:15:55,800
Eighty-nine, 88-

149
00:16:00,010 --> 00:16:01,050
One...

150
00:16:01,630 --> 00:16:02,930
...two, three, four...

151
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:08,930
...five. Where's six?

152
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:56,720
It took me a second or two,
but I figured out the sixth bomb...

153
00:16:56,930 --> 00:16:58,670
...was just a wild-goose chase.

154
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:03,720
You are different
from the other lesser beings. Faster.

155
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:06,880
Why?
-Lesser beings?

156
00:17:07,050 --> 00:17:08,380
What are you talking about?

157
00:17:11,050 --> 00:17:12,720
Eh? Wha-?

158
00:17:15,630 --> 00:17:16,670
What did you do?

159
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:19,180
I rewired it on the way down.

160
00:17:27,550 --> 00:17:30,510
Don't ever mess with my Iris.

161
00:18:10,090 --> 00:18:11,460
This little trip's been fun.

162
00:18:11,630 --> 00:18:13,840
Are you ever gonna tell me
where we're headed?

163
00:18:14,010 --> 00:18:17,090
To hell if you don't slow down.
What's wrong with you?

164
00:18:17,260 --> 00:18:19,760
Ever since you got out of the hospitaI...

165
00:18:19,930 --> 00:18:21,800
It was Korea.

166
00:18:22,670 --> 00:18:23,930
Changed everything.

167
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:26,090
Wars have a tendency to do that.

168
00:18:26,260 --> 00:18:28,800
Look, Ace, you know
that ever since I was a kid...

169
00:18:28,970 --> 00:18:32,550
...watching my old man fly,
I wanted to see the stars.

170
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,880
But the war and then the hospital...

171
00:18:35,340 --> 00:18:37,380
...it's like I'm damaged goods.

172
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:41,300
I can't get a first-class outfit
to take me on. And without a ride...

173
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:43,460
...I sure can't climb the pyramid.

174
00:18:44,380 --> 00:18:46,460
Slow down.
-Why bother?

175
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:49,670
You have to, kid, because we're here.

176
00:19:03,420 --> 00:19:06,180
It's where you get your second chance.

177
00:19:07,510 --> 00:19:09,670
<i>How did you know he was the commie?</i>

178
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:13,010
<i>He came back for the formula,
that's what nailed it.</i>

179
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:14,880
<i>He could've killed you.</i>

180
00:19:15,050 --> 00:19:17,670
<i>Like I always say,
when you know you're right...</i>

181
00:19:18,090 --> 00:19:19,670
<i>...it's worth taking a chance.</i>

182
00:19:20,140 --> 00:19:22,180
<i>Now, come here.</i>

183
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:45,880
Ace Morgan's recommendation
carries a lot of weight at Ferris Aircraft.

184
00:19:46,220 --> 00:19:48,220
I assume he spoke as well of us to you.

185
00:19:48,510 --> 00:19:53,050
He did. And I can't imagine anywhere else
I'd rather be right now, Miss Ferris.

186
00:19:54,010 --> 00:19:56,550
Do you have any questions?

187
00:19:57,220 --> 00:19:59,720
I'm surprised your father
isn't interviewing me.

188
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:02,720
Not that I mind, it's just that you're a-
-A woman?

189
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:05,880
My father trusts me with the day-to-day
operation of the company.

190
00:20:06,050 --> 00:20:09,090
If that's good enough for him, it ought to-
-Whoa, wait.

191
00:20:09,260 --> 00:20:13,840
I was only saying that you're a little young
to be running a major corporation.

192
00:20:14,260 --> 00:20:16,590
Oh. Oh, you're good, flyboy...

193
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:19,090
...but save it for the girls
in the typing pool.

194
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:20,590
One last question.

195
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:24,380
In your resume, there's a gap
between July and December of '53.

196
00:20:25,180 --> 00:20:27,380
I was in a VA hospitaI.

197
00:20:27,550 --> 00:20:28,590
Psych ward.

198
00:20:31,050 --> 00:20:33,590
Most people wouldn't talk about
this kind of thing...

199
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:35,720
...but I learned a lot about myself there.

200
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:38,930
I came out knowing who I really am
and what I really want.

201
00:20:40,340 --> 00:20:43,380
You report for training
and security clearance in two weeks.

202
00:20:44,090 --> 00:20:45,670
All right, let's celebrate.

203
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:48,010
Waiter, some champagne.

204
00:20:48,180 --> 00:20:51,510
Look, HaI,
I don't get involved with my employees.

205
00:20:51,670 --> 00:20:52,760
I understand, Carol...

206
00:20:53,140 --> 00:20:55,220
...but I don't start work
for two more weeks.

207
00:20:56,760 --> 00:20:58,180
Two glasses.

208
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:06,670
So where'd this hot tip come from, John?
-A source.

209
00:21:07,930 --> 00:21:09,800
WelI, I think I know your secret.

210
00:21:10,460 --> 00:21:12,050
You do?
-Hm.

211
00:21:12,300 --> 00:21:14,220
The tips you get from out of the blue...

212
00:21:14,380 --> 00:21:17,220
...those hunches of yours
that always turn out to be right.

213
00:21:18,510 --> 00:21:20,260
You're dating a fortuneteller.

214
00:21:20,630 --> 00:21:22,090
No, I-

215
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:25,800
Something like that.

216
00:21:35,420 --> 00:21:38,760
Try the back.
I'll see if I can pick this lock.

217
00:22:25,670 --> 00:22:27,090
You are the tribute.

218
00:22:27,260 --> 00:22:29,930
Yours is the glory
of nourishing the strength...

219
00:22:30,180 --> 00:22:32,260
...of The Centre.

220
00:22:44,090 --> 00:22:46,010
You okay, John?

221
00:22:55,590 --> 00:22:57,420
No, stay away.

222
00:22:57,590 --> 00:22:59,380
Stay away!

223
00:22:59,550 --> 00:23:02,260
Back off, you're scaring the boy.

224
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,840
You'll be alI right now that-

225
00:23:13,010 --> 00:23:14,930
You wilI be judged too.

226
00:23:15,970 --> 00:23:18,140
You wilI all be judged.

227
00:23:18,300 --> 00:23:22,180
Without The Centre, there is no holding.

228
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:26,010
The Centre? What's The Centre?

229
00:23:51,340 --> 00:23:52,840
<i>Jordan, do you copy?</i>

230
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:55,840
<i>Negative, Colonel Flagg, no Jordan here...</i>

231
00:23:56,630 --> 00:23:58,970
<i>-... just Spam in a can.
Cut the comedy.</i>

232
00:23:59,300 --> 00:24:01,630
Are you go for 72?

233
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:03,840
<i>Yes, Captain Personality.</i>

234
00:24:04,010 --> 00:24:06,460
<i>Jordan is go for exercise 72.</i>

235
00:24:06,930 --> 00:24:09,800
<i>Hit it.
-My pleasure.</i>

236
00:24:30,420 --> 00:24:34,340
Spam Jordan is now go for exercise 73.

237
00:24:35,300 --> 00:24:37,970
How's he doing?
-He's tough enough, that's for sure.

238
00:24:38,140 --> 00:24:41,260
But I'm getting sick of his attitude.
-He's a pilot, ColoneI Flagg.

239
00:24:41,420 --> 00:24:43,800
He's used to making decisions
and being in control.

240
00:24:43,970 --> 00:24:45,970
This training goes against his nature.

241
00:24:46,220 --> 00:24:48,510
Can't be helped.
It's all part of the big picture.

242
00:24:48,840 --> 00:24:51,180
Which he hasn't seen yet.

243
00:24:57,460 --> 00:24:58,630
CaroI.

244
