with high susceptibility.

304
00:29:15,050 --> 00:29:17,220
Getting into their minds.

305
00:29:17,380 --> 00:29:18,590
I felt it.

306
00:29:18,930 --> 00:29:22,090
Yes, your feelings. How-?

307
00:29:22,260 --> 00:29:24,420
Let's just say that's my secret.

308
00:29:24,590 --> 00:29:27,420
You came here because
you want to work together, true?

309
00:29:27,590 --> 00:29:30,140
True.
-Then we'll share our information.

310
00:29:31,140 --> 00:29:32,800
I've already collected some.

311
00:29:37,630 --> 00:29:38,930
Newspaper clippings.

312
00:29:39,090 --> 00:29:41,260
You'll have to do better than that.

313
00:29:41,760 --> 00:29:46,800
And one other thing, I'm not sure
what you are or where you come from...

314
00:29:46,970 --> 00:29:50,050
...but my instincts tell me
you're to be trusted.

315
00:29:50,220 --> 00:29:52,050
Make no mistake, though.

316
00:29:52,220 --> 00:29:54,840
I have a $70,000 sliver
of radioactive meteor...

317
00:29:55,010 --> 00:29:56,630
...to stop the one from Metropolis.

318
00:29:56,970 --> 00:30:01,010
With you, all I need is a penny
for a book of matches.

319
00:30:19,460 --> 00:30:22,760
What's the matter, Grodd,
feeling starved for attention?

320
00:30:50,090 --> 00:30:52,220
You're government property now, swifty.

321
00:30:52,380 --> 00:30:55,180
We're gonna find out
what makes you tick.

322
00:31:03,300 --> 00:31:04,720
Hey.
Did you see that?

323
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:06,760
Where did he go?

324
00:31:15,220 --> 00:31:17,380
What you got there, John?

325
00:31:18,300 --> 00:31:20,010
A kids' book?
-Not exactly.

326
00:31:20,180 --> 00:31:22,590
The author committed suicide
a while back.

327
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:24,760
He thought the world was about to end.

328
00:31:24,930 --> 00:31:26,840
You like this weird stuff, don't you?

329
00:31:27,010 --> 00:31:30,300
WelI, you should see what they got
in the interrogation room.

330
00:31:31,300 --> 00:31:33,260
He shot a cop on the parkway.

331
00:31:33,420 --> 00:31:35,090
Then we found his mother...

332
00:31:35,260 --> 00:31:37,090
...in his trunk.

333
00:31:37,460 --> 00:31:39,550
Mental case?
-Not your typical one.

334
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:42,180
This guy's a scientist.

335
00:31:44,930 --> 00:31:48,010
You're here to kill me, aren't you?
You're part of it.

336
00:31:48,180 --> 00:31:50,260
I'm not going to kill you.

337
00:31:50,420 --> 00:31:52,510
And what do you think I'm part of?

338
00:31:52,670 --> 00:31:54,760
The Centre. It's everywhere.

339
00:31:55,590 --> 00:31:57,220
What do you know about The Centre?

340
00:31:57,380 --> 00:32:00,260
It's gonna kill everyone.
I was trying to get away from it.

341
00:32:00,420 --> 00:32:02,050
How do you know alI this?

342
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:05,840
I just do. I can feel it.

343
